  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This scroll has 7 charges.</p><p> While holding it, you can use an action and expend 1 charge to speak its command word.</p><p> For the next minute, you know the direction of the nearest creature hostile to you within 60 feet, but not its distance from you.</p><p> The scroll can sense the presence of hostile creatures that are ethereal, invisible, disguised, or hidden, as well as those in plain sight.</p><p> The effect ends if you stop holding the scroll.</p><p> The scroll regains 1d6+1 expended charges daily at dawn.</p><p> If you expend the scroll's last charge, roll a d20.</p><p> On a 1, the scroll crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.</p><p></p>",
